Fetched : 2025-09-15T09:19:16.009484
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/trump-vs-fed-the-battle-over-governor-lisa-cook/slideshow/123892207.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Trump administration renewed its request to a federal appeals court to allow the firing of Federal Reserve Governor Lisa Cook. This move comes ahead of the Fed’s upcoming interest rate vote. The administration argues that Cook’s legal reasoning for remaining on the board is without merit. (Source: Reuters)
IANS
2/8
Cook’s Response
Lisa Cook’s lawyers countered that the Trump administration has not provided sufficient cause to remove her. They emphasized the risks to both the economy and the nation if a president could dismiss a Fed governor without proper justification.
AP
3/8
Historical Context
If successful, this would be the first time in the Fed’s 112-year history that a president has attempted to fire a governor. The move is seen as an unprecedented effort to influence the traditionally independent central bank.
ETMarkets.com
4/8
Trump’s Legal Argument
Trump’s lawyers argue that both the public and the executive branch share an interest in maintaining the Fed’s integrity. They claim that the president has statutory authority to remove governors “for cause” when such cause arises.
AP
5/8
Allegations Against Cook
Bill Pulte, a Trump appointee at Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, alleged that Cook misrepresented properties as primary residences, including an Atlanta condo and a home in Ann Arbor, Michigan. He submitted a criminal referral, which the Justice Department is investigating.
Getty Images
6/8
Cook’s Defense
Cook, the first Black woman to serve as a Fed governor, described the Atlanta condominium as a “vacation home” in a loan estimate. On a separate security clearance form, she called the property a “second home,” challenging claims of mortgage fraud.
AP
7/8
Court Ruling
A federal judge ruled that Cook’s removal was illegal, reinstating her to the Fed board. The administration subsequently appealed and requested an emergency ruling just before the Fed’s rate-setting meeting.
NYT News Service
8/8
Implications for the Fed
The case arrives as the Fed prepares to vote on interest rates, with most economists expecting a quarter-point reduction. The outcome could set a precedent regarding presidential influence over the central bank’s independence.
(Disclaimer: This slideshow has been sourced from Reuters)

