Title   : NBCC, HFCL, among 6 F&O stocks saw a high increase in futures open interest 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-15T03:31:21
Fetched : 2025-09-15T09:45:35.946941
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/nbcc-hfcl-among-6-fo-stocks-saw-a-high-increase-in-futures-open-interest/slideshow/123891229.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NBCC, HFCL, among 6 F&O stocks saw a high increase in futures open interest
1/7
Futures Surge
There was a notable surge in futures open interest for six stocks in the NSE F&O pack, contributing to a total increase in open interest of over 5.5% as of September 12, as compared to the previous trade. A significant uptick in futures open interest signifies a substantial growth in the number of active, unexpired futures contracts in a specific security. This uptrend reflects an increasing number of participants either initiating new positions or expanding the size of their existing positions within the futures market.
ETMarkets.com
2/7
NBCC (India)
OI: 6,81,00,500| Chg OI: 67,27,500 | Chg OI (%): 10.96
ETMarkets.com
3/7
Lodha Developers
OI: 98,17,650| Chg OI: 9,58,950 | Chg OI (%): 10.82
ETMarkets.com
4/7
HFCL
OI: 13,14,96,150| Chg OI: 1,14,10,050 | Chg OI (%): 9.5
ETMarkets.com
5/7
Godrej Consumer Products
OI: 97,66,000| Chg OI: 6,56,500 | Chg OI (%): 7.21
ETMarkets.com
6/7
KPIT Technologies
OI: 32,82,400| Chg OI: 1,93,200 | Chg OI (%): 6.25

