Title   : KRBL shares plunge nearly 10% as Independent Director quits over governance issues 
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-15T06:46:01
Fetched : 2025-09-15T10:02:17.554774
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/stock-markets/krbl-shares-plunge-nearly-10-as-independent-director-quits-over-governance-issues/article70051607.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
KRBL Limited shares tumbled nearly 10 per cent on Monday morning, trading at ₹400.60 on the NSE at 11:43 AM, down ₹43.50 from the previous close of ₹444.10. The stock opened at ₹406 and hit a high of ₹413.90 before declining to a low of ₹387.10.
The sharp decline followed the resignation of Independent Director Anil Kumar Chaudhary, who cited serious corporate governance concerns in his resignation letter dated September 8, 2025. The company informed stock exchanges about the resignation on September 13.
In his resignation letter, Chaudhary outlined multiple governance issues including inconsistencies in recording board meeting minutes, information being withheld from directors, unjust write-offs of export receivables, concerns over CSR fund usage, and arbitrary distribution of variable pay. He also flagged significant changes to the company’s object clause without proper discussion and undue interference by invitees in board proceedings.
Chaudhary stated he could no longer meaningfully contribute to the board’s functioning and found the prevailing dynamics inconsistent with effective governance principles. He confirmed there were no material reasons for his resignation beyond those mentioned in his letter.
The stock showed heavy selling pressure with traded volume reaching 65.91 lakh shares worth ₹264.34 crore. KRBL’s market capitalization stood at ₹9,113.25 crore, with deliverable quantity at 39.69 per cent of total trades, indicating significant investor concern over the governance issues.
Published on September 15, 2025

