Title   : Stocks to buy this week: IREDA, BEL among 7 stocks with potential upside of up to 21% 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-15T05:20:02
Fetched : 2025-09-15T10:38:16.282845
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/stocks-to-buy-this-week-ireda-bel-among-7-stocks-with-potential-upside-of-up-to-21/slideshow/123892971.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Nifty ended the previous week with gains of 1.5% with the index surpassing its immediate resistance at 25,100. Centrum Broking's Nilesh Jain said that Nifty trading above all key short-term and long-term moving averages is a positive sign and the strategy should be a buy on declines. ETMarkets has compiled 7 stocks to buy this week for a potential upside of 21%. Take a look!
Shares of IREDA jumped 1.3% last week and we can expect a short covering in the stock as charts show a positive trend. Strong support at Rs 144 is seen with resistance at Rs 137 levels. Buy on dips with the stop loss of Rs 137 and target of Rs 160-165 levels.
Shares of BEL rallied 8% last week and current trends show a positive outlook with bullish chart patterns. Buy with a stop loss of Rs 374 and target of Rs 420-440.
Shares of Glenmark Pharma ended 4% up WoW. It recovered from its retracement levels around 1,900 levels. Optimism on Trump's tariff is supportive for the pharma sector. Technically, it looks like an attractive buy. Place stop loss at Rs 2,040 and target at Rs 2,230-2,250.
Trident may benefit from a positive outcome of the US-India tariff talks. The stock gained 2.4% last week and a further upside for the targets up to 35 is expected. Place the stop loss at Rs 24.
Shares of Tech Mahindra rallied 3% last week triggering a bottom buying in the stock supported by substantial volumes. Buy this stock for targets of Rs 1,600 and Rs 1,620 levels. Place stop loss at Rs 1,460.
(Anuj Gupta, Ya Wealth Global Research)
Reuters
7/8
Buy Raymond Realty at Rs 643–637 | Target: Rs 700 | Upside: 9%
Raymond Realty is a newly listed demerged entity from Raymond has now given a trendline breakout after consolidation. The breakout indicates a potential change of trend and scope for a pullback rally. Buy in the range of Rs 643–637 with stop loss of Rs 610.
(Mehul Jitendra Kothari, Anand Rathi)
Agencies
8/8
Buy Lemon Tree Hotels at Rs 175.20 | Target: Rs 210 | Upside: 15%
Lemon Tree Hotels is a fundamental pick by SBI Securities with a view of 12 months. It is one of India’s leading hospitality companies with stock available at reasonable valuation. As of Q1, total inventory for the group stood at 18,431 rooms across 226 hotels.
(Sunny Agrawal, SBI Securities)
