Title   : Airfloa Rail, LT Elevator and Euro Pratik IPOs in focus
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-15T09:38:18
Fetched : 2025-09-15T10:43:08.689650
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/airfloa-rail-lt-elevator-and-euro-pratik-ipos-in-focus/article70052054.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The IPO market continues to stay active with a mix of and SME mainboard issues, attracting investor sentiment. From the oversubscribed Airfloa Rail Technology to L T Elevator’s modest offering and Euro Pratik Sales’ sizeable OFS, investors are keeping a close eye on subscription trends, grey market signals and listing dates.
Airfloa Rail Technology’s SME IPO draws massive interest
Airfloa Rail Technology launched its SME IPO on the BSE-SME platform with an issue size of ₹91.10 crore through a fresh issue of 65.07 lakh shares. The price band was fixed at ₹133–₹140 per share with a minimum lot size of 1,000 shares.
The offer opened on September 11, 2025 and concludes, today September 15, 2025, with allotment scheduled on September 16 and listing on September 18, 2025. The IPO witnessed overwhelming response with overall subscription over 132 times at the time of writing. As per unlisted market, the shares are commanding a strong premium, indicating a potential bumper listing.
L T Elevator’s SME IPO gains steady traction
L T Elevator’s SME IPO is a smaller issue worth ₹39.37 crore, consisting of 50.48 lakh fresh equity shares. The company set the price band at ₹76–₹78 per share, with a minimum lot size of 1,600 shares. The IPO opened on September 12, 2025, and closes on September 16, 2025. Allotment will be finalized on September 17, and listing is expected on September 19, 2025. As of Day 2, the issue has been oversubscribed by 2 times.
Euro Pratik Sales’ mainboard IPO opens tomorrow
Euro Pratik Sales is a mainboard IPO worth ₹451.31 crore, comprising entirely an offer-for-sale of 1.83 crore shares. The price band is set at ₹235–₹247 per share, with a minimum lot size of 60 shares. The IPO window will remain open from September 16-18, with allotment expected on September 19, and listing on September 23, 2025, on both NSE and BSE.
Upcoming IPO, listings on D-Street
Apart from these, investors can expect a busy pipeline of offerings in the coming week. VMS TMT is one of the mainboard IPOs scheduled to open, while three SME IPOs are also lined up for subscription.
On the mainboard segment, shares of Urban Company, Dev Accelerator and Shringar House of Mangalsutra will debut on bourses on September 17. In addition, nearly nine SME IPOs will list this week, including Krupalu Metals.
Published on September 15, 2025

Title   : TVS Motor, ALT Mobility partner to deploy 3,000 e-three wheelers this fiscal
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-15T08:24:34
Fetched : 2025-09-15T10:43:08.689650
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/tvs-motor-alt-mobility-partner-to-deploy-3000-e-three-wheelers-this-fiscal/article70051886.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TVS Motor Company on Monday said it has inked a pact with leasing and asset management company ALT Mobility to deploy 3,000 electric three-wheelers this fiscal year.
As part of the collaboration, TVS will provide vehicles, while ALT Mobility will procure, lease, and finance them through its ecosystem.
The models, variants, and specifications will be jointly finalised to best serve customer needs, and the vehicles will be rolled out through TVS Motor's extensive network of authorised dealers and ALT's point of sales across India, the company said in a statement.
The vehicles will be deployed under ALT's drive-to-own leasing model to individual drivers and fleet operators for cargo and passenger transportation, it added.
"This collaboration with ALT Mobility is a significant step towards enabling sustainable urban and last-mile mobility at scale," TVS Motor Company Business Head --Commercial Mobility Rajat Gupta said.
Anuj Gupta, Co-founder & CBO, ALT Mobility, said partnering with TVS Motor Company gives the company access to industry-leading vehicles and technology, which will help it scale leasing and fleet operations effectively.
Published on September 15, 2025

